The '''Watarai clan''' (度会氏, Watarai-uji) is a Japanese [[:en:Clan|Clan]] whose family name is derived from "Watarai." Until the early [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]], many members of this clan served as [[shrine priests]] (negi) of the [[Toyōke Daijingū|Gekū]] (Outer Shrine) of [[Ise Grand Shrine|Ise Jingū]] in a [[:en:Hereditary|Hereditary]] capacity.

